pickle /ˈpɪkəl/

(pickling,pickled,pickles) 

1. N-PLURAL Pickles are vegetables or fruit, sometimes cut into pieces, which have been kept in vinegar or salt water for a long time so that they have a strong, sharp taste. 泡菜 

例： ...a bowl of sliced pickles in lemon juice. …一碗浸在柠檬汁中的泡菜片。 

2. N-MASS Pickle is a cold spicy sauce with pieces of vegetables and fruit in it. 泡菜酱 

例： ...jars of pickle. …成罐的泡菜酱。 

3. V-T When you pickle food, you keep it in vinegar or salt water so that it does not go bad and it develops a strong, sharp taste. 腌制 

例： Select your favourite fruit or veg and pickle them while they are still fresh. 挑选你最喜欢的水果或蔬菜，趁新鲜腌制起来。

